If I have an open bug that affects v2.0, and I create version 2.1, then in most cases, the bug also affects v2.1.  It would be nice if JIRA reflected this, by providing an easy way to bulk-set the Affects version to include a newly defined version.

The idea is that after a new version is created, one would like want to *add* this version as an "affected version" to all unresolved bugs, as they are likely also affected. The behaviour should not be forced on the administrator, so a bulk-edit wizard should be used here.

