I frequently put together searches/filters with several dozen, or more issues in the result set. As I next through the issues, JIRA has an indicator "Issue x of y issue(s)", which is handy. But when I "Return to Search" there's no easy way to find where I was on the list (in the Browser view). So, if for example, I am working on issue 33 of 108, and I return to the search it would be nice to have a column that had that number displayed so I could more easily jump to it. It would make sense to simply add that "Index" column in the issue navigator, although it would not make sense for it to be a sortable column - that would defeat the purpose, since I want to sort in a particular way but be able to find my issues quickly.

